tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Finished T39 at the Florida Qualifying Tournament, earning conditional status for the Mackenzie Tour's 2015 season. Best season finish was T28 at the Cape Breton Classic in September.

2012: Played eight Mackenzie Tour events. Best finish of the year was T38 at The Players Cup.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Captured two collegiate wins at Kent State and earned 2010 Mid-American Conference Player of the Year honors as a junior. Was a two-time all-conference selection for the Golden Flashes (in 2009 and 2010).
tourBios.personal: Favorite course is The National Golf Club and favorite professional teams are Kent State, the Toronto Maple Leafs and the Philadelphia Eagles...In honor of his alma mater uses a Kent State headcover...Favorite city to visit is Chicago, and his favorite athletes are Tiger Woods and LeBron James...Has two sisters...Twitter is @brettcairns89.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA T was T28th in 2015 at the Cape Breton Celtic Classic presented by PC Financial.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T24th in Current Par or Better Streak on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA TOUR Canada.
